The paper discusses algorithms for data detection and precoding in massive multiuser MIMO systems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The proposed algorithms also involve coordination and optimization, which are relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses parallelization and optimization of computations, which are relevant to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
